OL,6,FMohammadi targeted 11 victims in his
OL,7,Ffive-month crime spree between October
OL,8,F24, 2024 and March 24, 2025. A jury
OL,9,Ffound him guilty of 10 counts of
OL,10,Fburgling a dwelling, nine of fraud by
OL,11,Ffalse representation and one of theft
OL,12,Fand jailed for five years.
OL,14,FHotak committed multiple offences
OL,15,Fbetween October 24, 2024 and 23
OL,16,FDecember 23, 2024. He was convicted of
OL,17,Ffive counts of burgling a dwelling,
OL,18,Ffive of fraud by false representation
OL,19,Fand one of theft. He recieved a three
OL,20,Fand a half year sentence.
